                    <span>I am simpithetic to the previous two readers. They obviously did not want to learn of the religion. if they had they would have learned much more as I did learn.
<br />The first thing to note is that this book is on of the Dalai Lama's books. In it he incorporates experiences of his own life to portray that even if you don't become an oficial Buddhist you can still incorporate these pratices into your own life. The book give you fully detailed explainations on each step of the path. At the end of every section is a Summary of Daily Practice which simplifies the section so you don't fall behind or get lost. 
<br />The book also explains how to use the religion in daily life and how to treat Buddhism properly. This book Inspired me to become a Buddhist, I only hope that it inspires you.</span>
                  
